<li id="cite_note-99"><b><a href="#cite_ref-99" title="">^</a></b> Rae E. Unzicker, Kate P. Wolters, Debra Robinson et al. <a href="http://www.ncd.gov/newsroom/publications/2000/privileges.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ncd.gov/newsroom/publications/2000/privileges.htm" rel="nofollow">From Privileges to Rights: People Labeled with Psychiatric Disabilities Speak for Themselves</a>. <a href="/wiki/National_Council_on_Disability" title="National Council on Disability">National Council on Disability</a> 20 January 2000.</li>
<li id="cite_note-100"><b><a href="#cite_ref-100" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTreatment_Protocol_Project2009">Treatment Protocol Project (2003). <i>Acute inpatient psychiatric care: A source book</i>. Darlinghurst, Australia: World Health Organisation. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0957807317" class="internal">ISBN 0-9578073-1-7</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/223935527" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/223935527" rel="nofollow">223935527</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Acute+inpatient+psychiatric+care%3A+A+source+book&amp;rft.aulast=Treatment+Protocol+Project&amp;rft.au=Treatment+Protocol+Project&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.place=Darlinghurst%2C+Australia&amp;rft.pub=World+Health+%0AOrganisation&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/223935527&amp;rft.isbn=0-9578073-1-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Psychiatry"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
